{"name": "spotifython-cli", "metadata": {"name": "spotifython-cli", "version": "0.3.4", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: End Users/Desktop", "License :: OSI Approved :: GNU General Public License v3 (GPLv3)", "Natural Language :: English", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Topic :: Internet", "Topic :: Utilities", "Typing :: Typed"], "home_page": "https://github.com/vawvaw/spotifython-cli", "license": "GPLv3", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["spotifython", "click"], "summary": "A command line interface for spotifython intended for use with spotifyd", "upload_time": 1735390144}, "documentation": ["# spotifython-cli\n\nA command line interface to the Spotify API using [spotifython](https://github.com/vawvaw/spotifython) as a backend.\nThis tool is developed for the use in scripting on linux and is integrated with the spotifyd player.\nAll API access except playback modification is readonly.\n\n## Installation\n\n**python 3.10 or higher is required**\n\n```sh\n# Linux/macOS\npython3 -m pip install -U spotifython-cli\n```\n\n```sh\n# Windows\npy -3 -m pip install -U spotifython-cli\n```\n\nTo install the development version, run:\n\n```sh\ngit clone https://github.com/vawvaw/spotifython-cli\ncd spotipython-cli\npython3 -m pip install -U .\n```\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- [spotifyd](https://github.com/Spotifyd/spotifyd) for player integration\n- `dmenu` for interactive selection of content\n\n## Example\n\n```sh\nspotifython-cli play\n```\n\nWith dmenu:\n\n```sh\nspotifython-cli play --queue 'saved@#ask@#ask'\n```\n\nOr for scripting:\n\n```sh\nspotifython-cli metadata --format \"{title:.30} - {artist_name:.18}\"\n```\n\n## Config\n\n`~/.config/spotifython-cli/config`\n\n```\n[Authentication]\nclient_id = \"your client id\nclient_secret = \"your client secret\"\n# alternative to client_secret\nclient_secret_command = \"cat /path/to/client_secret\"\n\n[spotifyd]\nnotify = true   # optional\n\n[playback]\ndevice_id = \"your playback device\"  # optional\n\n[interface]\n# dmenu with custom options or a program with a similar interface (gets options on stdin and writes results to stdout)\ndmenu_cmdline = dmenu -i -l 50 -p {prompt} # optional\n```\n\nFor help on how to obtain client id and secret refer to the [spotifython documentation](https://github.com/vawvaw/spotifython).\n"], "modules": [{"name": "spotifython_cli", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "spotifython_cli.load_authentication", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cache_dir", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "config", "type": {"name": "configparser.ConfigParser", "xref": {"fqname": "configparser.ConfigParser", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "spotifython.Authentication", "xref": {"fqname": "spotifython.Authentication", "project": "spotifython"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "spotifython_cli.dmenu_query", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "prompt", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "options", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "config", "type": {"name": "configparser.ConfigParser", "xref": {"fqname": "configparser.ConfigParser", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "spotifython_cli.dmenu_select", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "prompt", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "options", "type": {"name": "Mapping", "xref": {"fqname": "collections.abc.Mapping", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "spotifython.Cacheable", "xref": {"fqname": "spotifython.Cacheable", "project": "spotifython"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "config", "type": {"name": "configparser.ConfigParser", "xref": {"fqname": "configparser.ConfigParser", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "spotifython.Cacheable", "xref": {"fqname": "spotifython.Cacheable", "project": "spotifython"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "spotifython_cli.cli", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ctx", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "verbose", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "device_id", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "config", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "spotifython_cli.play", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "context", "type": {"name": "click.Context", "xref": {"fqname": "click.Context", "project": "click"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "shuffle", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "reverse", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "queue", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "from_ask", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "to_ask", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "elements", "type": {"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "spotifython.URI", "xref": {"fqname": "spotifython.URI", "project": "spotifython"}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["start playback\n\n\nElements begin with either a spotify uri or the literal string \"search\" or \"saved\". Specifiers are seperated by an '@'.\n\nAfter \"saved\" must be the name of a saved playlist, saved album or \"#saved tracks\".\n\nAfter \"search\" must be the search term. The search results will be displayed using the config value `interface.dmenu_cmdline`. If that is not specicied, the first song will be used.\n\nAfter a collection is selected, the next literal will select the track.\nThe special value \"#all\" selects all entries.\nIf no selector is specified, the implementation will default to \"#ask\".\nIf a track is selected, this will be ignored.\n\nEvery literal may be replaced by \"#ask\" in which case `interface.dmenu_cmdline` will be used.\nA backslash '\\' can be used to escape a literal '@', '#' or '\\'."]}, {"name": "spotifython_cli.pause", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "context", "type": {"name": "click.Context", "xref": {"fqname": "click.Context", "project": "click"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["pause playback"]}, {"name": "spotifython_cli.play_pause", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "context", "type": {"name": "click.Context", "xref": {"fqname": "click.Context", "project": 